Title: Chapter One: The Vanishing of Will Byers

Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard

Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Jessie Nickson-Lopez
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Mike hides the mysterious girl in his house. Joyce gets a strange phone call.

Title: Chapter Four: The Body
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Justin Doble
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Refusing to believe Will is dead, Joyce tries to connect with her son. The boys give Eleven a makeover. Jonathan and Nancy form an unlikely alliance.

Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Alison Tatlock
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard

Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Jessie Nickson-Lopez
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Hopper and Joyce find the truth about the lab's experiments. After their fight, the boys look for the missing Eleven.

Title: Chapter Seven: The Bathtub
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Justin Doble
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: The government comes searching for Eleven. Eleven looks for Will and Barb in the Upside Down.

Title: Chapter Eight: The Upside Down
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Paul Dichter
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard

Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Jessie Nickson-Lopez
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard

Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Jessie Nickson-Lopez

Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Justin Doble
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Dustin adopts a strange new pet, and Eleven grows increasingly impatient. A well-meaning Bob urges Will to stand up to his fears.

Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Paul Dichter
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: An ailing Will opens up to Joyce -- with disturbing results. While Hopper digs for the truth, Eleven unearths a surprising discovery.

Title: Chapter Five: Dig Dug
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Jessie Nickson-Lopez
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Nancy and Jonathan swap conspiracy theories with a new ally as Eleven searches for someone from her past. "Bob the Brain" tackles a difficult problem.

Title: Chapter Six: The Spy
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Kate Trefry
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Will's connection to a shadowy evil grows stronger but no one's quite sure how to stop it. Elsewhere, Dustin and Steve forge an unlikely bond.

Title: Chapter Seven: The Lost Sister
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Justin Doble
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Psychic visions draw Eleven to a band of violent outcasts and an angry girl with a shadowy past.

Title: Chapter Eight: The Mind Flayer
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Jessie Nickson-Lopez
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard

Title: Chapter Nine: The Gate
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Jessie Nickson-Lopez
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Eleven makes plans to finish what she started while the survivors turn up the heat on the monstrous force that's holding Will hostage.

Title: Chapter One: Suzie, Do You Copy?
Writer: Matt Duffer, Ross Duffer, Paul Dichter
Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
Plot: Summer brings new jobs and budding romance. But the mood shifts when Dustin's radio picks up a Russian broadcast, and Will senses something is wrong.

Actors: Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard
